procedures.name: Blood Sampling
procedures.label: Blood Draw
procedures.description: Collection of venous blood samples for pharmacokinetic (PK), pharmacodynamic (PD), clinical safety laboratory assessments (serum chemistry, hematology, coagulation), and pregnancy testing.

code.decode: Collection of venous blood by venipuncture

procedures.name: Urine Collection
procedures.label: Urine Sample Collection
procedures.description: Collection of urine for urinalysis, drug screening, pregnancy testing, and 24-hour measurement of copper and molybdenum content.

code.decode: Urinalysis, by dip stick or tablet reagent for bilirubin, glucose, hemoglobin, ketones, leukocytes, nitrite, pH, protein, specific gravity, urobilinogen, any number of these constituents; non-automated, without microscopy

procedures.name: Fecal Collection
procedures.label: Stool Sample Collection
procedures.description: Collection of individual fecal samples for measurement of copper and molybdenum content.

procedures.name: Physical Examination
procedures.label: Physical Exam
procedures.description: A complete physical examination including, at a minimum, assessments of the cardiovascular, respiratory, gastrointestinal, and neurological systems.

procedures.name: Vital Signs Measurement
procedures.label: Vital Signs
procedures.description: Measurement of body temperature, heart rate, respiratory rate, and systolic and diastolic blood pressure.

procedures.name: 12-lead Electrocardiogram
procedures.label: ECG
procedures.description: Triplicate 12-lead ECG to assess heart rate and intervals (PR, QRS, QT and QTc).

code.decode: Electrocardiogram, routine ECG with at least 12 leads; with interpretation and report

procedures.name: Urine Drug Screen
procedures.label: Drug Screen
procedures.description: Screening test for drug use via urine sample.

procedures.name: Infectious Disease Screening
procedures.label: HIV, Hep B/C Screen
procedures.description: Screening for HIV, hepatitis B and C.

procedures.name: Medical History Collection
procedures.label: Medical History
procedures.description: Collection of participant medical history, demographics, Wilson disease history, and prior treatments.

procedures.name: Anthropometric Measurements
procedures.label: Height, Weight, BMI
procedures.description: Measurement of height, weight, and calculation of Body Mass Index (BMI).

procedures.name: Adverse Event Monitoring
procedures.label: AE Monitoring
procedures.description: Ongoing monitoring and collection of adverse event (AE) and serious adverse event (SAE) information.

procedures.name: Bowel and Urine Monitoring
procedures.label: Intake/Output Monitoring
procedures.description: Monitoring of urination and bowel movements.

procedures.name: Food and Fluid Collection
procedures.label: Dietary Sample Collection
procedures.description: Collection of samples of all meal and fluid batches for measurement of copper and molybdenum content.

procedures.name: Neurological Monitoring
procedures.label: Neurological Monitoring
procedures.description: Regular monitoring for neurologic adverse events, including neurological worsening or peripheral neuropathy.

medicalDevices.name: Cannula
medicalDevices.label: IV Cannula
medicalDevices.description: A cannula may be placed to minimize needle sticks for repeated blood draws.

medicalDevices.name: Automated Blood Pressure and Heart Rate Monitor
medicalDevices.label: Automated BP Monitor
medicalDevices.description: A completely automated device for assessing blood pressure and heart rate measurements.

medicalDevices.name: 12-lead Electrocardiogram Machine
medicalDevices.label: ECG Machine
medicalDevices.description: Device used to perform triplicate 12-lead ECGs.
